---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const title = 'Privacy Policy | truckaccidentcalc.com';
const description = 'How truckaccidentcalc.com collects, uses, and shares visitor and lead information, including data shared with attorneys through our case-review tool.';
---
<BaseLayout title={title} description={description}>
  <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
  <p><em>Last updated: July 2026.</em></p>

  <p>This page explains what information truckaccidentcalc.com collects, how it's used, and — because this site includes a tool that connects you with attorneys — specifically what happens to your information if you use that tool. Two separate things happen on this site, and this policy treats them separately: reading the calculator and guides (anonymous, nothing collected), and using the "Truck Accident" case-review form (collects your contact information and shares it with attorneys). Only the second one involves your personal data.</p>

  <h2>What we collect</h2>

  <h3>Using the calculator and guides</h3>
  <p>The settlement calculator on our homepage runs entirely in your browser. Numbers you enter are <em>not</em> sent to our server, not stored, not logged, and not transmitted to third parties. Reading the calculator, methodology, or guide pages does not require an account, a form, or any personal information.</p>

  <h3>If you submit the case-review / lead form</h3>
  <p>If you fill out and submit the "Truck Accident" case-review form on this site, we collect the information you enter — typically your name, phone number, email address, and details about your situation — along with a timestamp and record of the consent language you agreed to. <strong>This is the only way personal information leaves your browser on this site.</strong> Submitting this form is always optional; you can use the calculator and read every guide on this site without ever seeing or completing it.</p>

  <h3>What you send us directly</h3>
  <p>If you email the editorial team at <a href="mailto:hey@theclicklab.agency">hey@theclicklab.agency</a>, we receive your email address and message contents. We don't have signup forms, comment sections, or other user accounts on this site.</p>

  <h3>Server logs and analytics</h3>
  <p>Our hosting provider records standard server access logs (IP address, request URL, user agent, timestamp) for security and reliability purposes. We may use a privacy-respecting analytics tool to count page views and understand which pages are popular. We do not use Google Analytics with default settings and we do not build behavioral profiles of individual visitors.</p>

  <h3>Advertising</h3>
  <p>This site shows ads through Google AdSense. Google and its advertising partners use cookies and similar technologies to serve ads based on a visitor's prior visits to our site and other sites. You can opt out of personalized advertising at <a href="https://www.google.com/settings/ads" rel="noopener">Google Ads Settings</a> or at <a href="https://www.aboutads.info" rel="noopener">aboutads.info</a>. For visitors in the EU/EEA/UK, AdSense's <a href="https://policies.google.com/technologies/partner-sites" rel="noopener">partner site policy</a> describes the legal basis and your rights.</p>

  <h2>How we use and share what we collect</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Email you send us:</strong> we use it to respond to your message. We don't add you to a mailing list. We don't share it with anyone outside our small editorial team unless you tell us to.</li>
    <li><strong>Server logs:</strong> security, abuse prevention, debugging, and very rough traffic understanding.</li>
    <li><strong>Advertising cookies:</strong> set and read by Google and its ad partners, not by us. We don't have access to who you are individually; AdSense reports give us aggregate ad performance data only.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Case-review form submissions — shared with attorneys</h3>
  <p><strong>If you submit the case-review form, your name, phone number, email address, and case details are shared with one or more attorneys or their agents licensed to practice in your jurisdiction, so they can evaluate your situation and contact you about it.</strong> The Click Lab Agency LLC, which operates truckaccidentcalc.com, is not a law firm, does not provide legal advice, and does not vet, endorse, or guarantee the attorneys in this network. Submitting the form does not create an attorney-client relationship with The Click Lab Agency LLC or with any attorney until and unless that attorney separately agrees to represent you. The Click Lab Agency LLC may be compensated for these referrals. This arrangement is disclosed on the form itself at the point of submission.</p>
  <p>By submitting the form, you separately consent to be contacted by phone, text, and email — including by automated dialing technology — by The Click Lab Agency LLC and the attorneys or agents your information is shared with. That consent is not required to use any other part of this site, and you can decline it by not submitting the form.</p>

  <h2>Your choices</h2>
  <p><strong>The simplest opt-out is not to submit the case-review form.</strong> Nothing about your visit is shared with any attorney unless you complete and submit it yourself.</p>
  <p>If you've already submitted the form and want to stop being contacted, email <a href="mailto:hey@theclicklab.agency">hey@theclicklab.agency</a> with the subject line <code>[OPT-OUT]</code>, or visit <a href="https://theclicklab.agency/optout" target="_blank" rel="noopener">theclicklab.agency/optout</a>. We will notify the attorney or agent your information was shared with and remove you from further outreach on our end.</p>
  <p>Browser-level: most modern browsers let you block third-party cookies, which limits AdSense's ability to personalize ads. The site works fine with cookies blocked &mdash; you'll still see ads, they just won't be personalized. Cookie-level: <a href="https://www.google.com/settings/ads" rel="noopener">Google Ads Settings</a> lets you turn off personalized advertising while keeping the rest of your Google experience.</p>
  <p>For California residents: sharing your information with attorneys in exchange for compensation may constitute a "sale" or "share" of personal information under the CCPA/CPRA. You have the right to opt out of that sale/share — the easiest way is not submitting the case-review form; to exercise this right after submission, email <a href="mailto:hey@theclicklab.agency">hey@theclicklab.agency</a> with the subject line <code>[CCPA OPT-OUT]</code>. We do not sell or share data collected only through anonymous site browsing (i.e., if you never submit the form).</p>
  <p>For GDPR / UK GDPR rights (access, rectification, erasure, portability, objection, restriction) — including for case-review form data, where the legal basis is your consent, withdrawable at any time — or CCPA rights (know, delete, opt out of sale, non-discrimination), email <a href="mailto:hey@theclicklab.agency">hey@theclicklab.agency</a> with the subject line <code>[PRIVACY REQUEST]</code>. We respond within the legally required window for the applicable jurisdiction.</p>

  <h2>Children</h2>
  <p>This site is not directed at children under 16, and the case-review form is not intended for use by anyone under 18 (the form itself requires confirming you are 18 or older). We don't knowingly collect information from children. If you believe a child has sent us information, email us and we will delete it.</p>

  <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
  <p>If we materially change how we handle visitor data — especially anything affecting the case-review form — we'll update this page and update the "last updated" date at the top.</p>

  <h2>Contact about privacy</h2>
  <p>Privacy questions: <a href="mailto:hey@theclicklab.agency">hey@theclicklab.agency</a> with subject line <code>[PRIVACY]</code>.</p>
</BaseLayout>
